<placeName cert="high">Karanis</placeName></head><div lang="grc" part="N" type="edition"><ab part="N">
    <lb n="1"/>Πτολεμαῖος τῷ πατρὶ χαίρειν. 

    <lb n="2"/><choice><corr>γινώσειν</corr><sic>γεινωσκιν</sic></choice> σε θέλω καὶ τὴν μη-

    <lb n="3"/>τέρα μου ὅτι σιωπητικοῦ τῆς 

    <lb n="4"/><choice><corr>κλίνης</corr><sic>κλεινης</sic></choice> <expan><ex cert="high">δραχμαὶ</ex></expan> <num value="24">κδ</num> καὶ τόπου ἄλλαι <expan><ex cert="high">δραχμαὶ</ex></expan> <num value="22">κβ</num>. 

    <lb n="5"/>λογισάμενος οὖν ἦρκα ἀγορανο-

    <lb n="6"/>μίαν <hi rend="diaeresis">ἵ</hi>να μήτε σιωπητικοῦ μήτε 

    <lb n="7"/>τόπου δῶ, ἀλλὰ καὶ διπλᾶ μέρη λαμ-

    <lb n="8"/>βάνω καὶ χορηγῶ αὐτοῖς ξύλα. 

    <lb n="9"/>ἀπ᾽ ἐντεῦθεν οὖν φρόντισον καὶ 

    <lb n="10"/>ἐὰν ἀναβῇς λήμψῃ τὸ ναῦλον 

    <lb n="11"/>τῶν ὄνων. χρεία γάρ ἐστιν <num value="5">ε</num> 

    <lb n="12"/>γόμων. ἐὰν δὲ χρεία μου <choice><corr>ᾖ</corr><sic>ην</sic></choice> <choice><corr>πέμ-

    <lb n="13"/>ψον</corr><sic>πεμψεν</sic></choice> μοι φάσιν καὶ καταβήσομαι 

    <lb n="14"/>μετὰ ἄλλων δύο <num value="2"/> φίλων <hi rend="diaeresis">ἵ</hi>να μὴ σὺ 

    <lb n="15"/>κοπιᾷς. καὶ γὰρ <choice><corr>ἀντειπεῖν</corr><sic>αντιπιν</sic></choice> ἄνθρωπος 

    <lb n="16"/>οὐ δύναται τῷ κυρίωι Σαράπιδι. ἄλλη 

    <lb n="17"/>γὰρ δίμηνός ἐστιν <choice><corr>ἕως</corr><sic>ως</sic></choice> τῆς 

    <lb n="18"/><choice><corr>κλίνης</corr><sic>κλεινης</sic></choice>. ἐὰν δύνῃ τῷ σῷ ὄνῳ 

    <lb n="19"/>ἀνενέγκαι αὐτά ἀνένεγκον καὶ 

    <lb n="20"/><choice><corr>εὑρήσεις</corr><sic>ευρησης</sic></choice> εἰς τὴν δαπάνην σου 

    <lb n="21"/>τὰς δραχμάς. 

    <lb n="22"/><handShift new="m2"/> <choice><corr>ἔρρωσο</corr><sic>ερρωσσο</sic></choice>. </ab></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" type="description"><p><rs cert="high" type="material">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" subtype="textDate" type="commentary"><p><date notAfter="250" notBefore="201" type="textDate">1. Hälfte III</date></p></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" subtype="principalEdition" type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl subtype="principal" type="publication"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Mich.</title><biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">511</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="Trismegistos"><biblScope type="numbers">30511</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP"><series>0163</series>; <biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">511</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" href="0163;8;511" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" type="Perseus">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" subtype="corrections" type="bibliography"><head>BL-Einträge nach BL-Konkordanz</head><bibl type="BL"><biblScope type="volume">VIII</biblScope>, S. <biblScope type="pages">215</biblScope></bibl></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" subtype="illustrations" type="bibliography"><p><bibl type="illustration">Plate VII</bibl></p></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" subtype="translations" type="bibliography"><head>Übersetzungen</head><listBibl lang="de"><head lang="de">Deutsch:</head><bibl type="translations">Metzger, Nachrichten aus dem Wüstensand (1974), Nr. 69</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" subtype="locations" type="history"><p><placeName cert="high" type="ancientFindspot">Memphis oder Ptolemais Euergetis</placeName> (<geogName cert="high" type="nome">Arsinoites</geogName>), <geogName cert="high" key="Aegyptus" type="ancientRegion">Egypt</geogName></p></div><div n="meta.30511" part="N" type="figure"><p><figure href="http://wwwapp.cc.columbia.edu/ldpd/app/api